  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging docs: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Monitor/Logging/ -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nAs an user, I expect besu to ignore the values passed if this warning comes up:\r\n`2022-08-26 14:43:18.150+10:00 | main | WARN  | Besu | --fast-sync-min-peers has been ignored because --sync-mode was not defined on the command line.`\r\n\r\n\r\ncommand used:\r\n`besu --network=goerli --fast-sync-min-peers=4`\r\n\r\nLogs:\r\n```\r\n2022-08-26 14:43:17.984+10:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Using LibEthPairings native alt bn128\r\n2022-08-26 14:43:17.986+10:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Using the native implementation of the signature algorithm\r\n2022-08-26 14:43:17.989+10:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Using the Java implementation of the blake2bf algorithm\r\n2022-08-26 14:43:17.991+10:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Starting Besu version: besu/v22.7.2-dev-80b79504/osx-aarch_64/openjdk-java-18\r\n2022-08-26 14:43:18.150+10:00 | main | WARN  | Besu | --fast-sync-min-peers has been ignored because --sync-mode was not defined on the command line.\r\n```\r\n...\r\n`2022-08-26 14:43:20.029+10:00 | main | INFO  | WaitForPeersTask | Waiting for 4 total peers to connect. 0 peers currently connected.`\r\n\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nWhen using fast-sync mode don't log the alert and use the value passed in --fast-sync-min-peers\r\nWhen using full-sync warn that --fast-sync-min-peers can't be used with full-sync\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** No warning since the default sync-mode for goerli is fast-sync\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** Warning that the value passed for --fast-sync-min-peers has been ignored but applies/uses the value later when looking for peers\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** Every time besu starts\r\n",
